{{Politics of Panama}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Panama]] on 15 December 1940.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p518 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> Voters were asked whether the [[Constitution of Panama|new constitution]] should be enacted. A reported 98.7% voted in favour.<ref>Nohlen, p524</ref>
